The paper proposes a new search procedure for black-box constraint programming solvers, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the experimental results on a variety of benchmarks, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the comparison with other heuristics, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
